  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Combating Gender-based violence and enhancing economic empowerment of women in Northern Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(1) Improve the understanding among all stakeholders of targeted communities on GBV.
(2) Strengthening traditional and institutional mechanisms for prevention, mediation and response to GBV 
(3) Strengthening economic opportunities and self reliance of women and girls
(4) Strengthening the capacity of women and girls for personal development</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The GOAL of the project is to reduce vulnerability of women and girls to GBV (physical, sexual, emotional and socio &#x2013; economic) in Uganda, and empowering them to become self &#x2013; reliant, economically and otherwise.

The PURPOSE is to contribute to the reduction of incidence of GBV against women in Amuru and Adjumani districts of Northern Uganda. The main action for achieving our purpose will include raising awareness and capacity building on prevention of GBV against women and girls in communities, improving their access to economic opportunities through cash transfers and VSLAs, and ensuring their personal development through life skills training.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Women: refers to women with partners and widows vulnerable to/victims of various types of GBV, ages 18 &#x2013; 60 years; Men: refers to partners/husbands of women trainees (CT and non &#x2013; CT beneficiaries), ages 14 &#x2013; 60 years;Out of School Girls and Boys: refers to child heads and those living with partners or parents, 14 &#x2013; 18 years
In &#x2013; school Girls and Boys: refers to children with parents and in school, ages 14 &#x2013; 18 years</narrative>
  </description>
